compare(String, String) - 类 中的静态方法org.sfandroid.hooklib.utils.StringUtils
Compare two Strings lexicographically, as per String.compareTo(String), returning : int = 0, if str1 is equal to str2 (or both null) int < 0, if str1 is less than str2 int > 0, if str1 is greater than str2 This is a null safe version of : str1.compareTo(str2) null value is considered less than non-null value.
compare(String, String, boolean) - 类 中的静态方法org.sfandroid.hooklib.utils.StringUtils
Compare two Strings lexicographically, as per String.compareTo(String), returning : int = 0, if str1 is equal to str2 (or both null) int < 0, if str1 is less than str2 int > 0, if str1 is greater than str2 This is a null safe version of : str1.compareTo(str2) null inputs are handled according to the nullIsLess parameter.
